Table 1.1.11. Real Gross Domestic Product: Percent Change From Quarter One Year Ago
Last Revised on: April 27, 2023 - Next Release Date May 25, 2023

column2: Net exports of goods and services
Government consumption expenditures and gross investment
Final sales to private domestic purchasers1
Gross domestic purchases excluding food and energy3
Gross domestic product excluding food and energy1
Personal consumption expenditures excluding food and energy3
Market-based PCE excluding food and energy4

column1: 1. Final sales to domestic purchasers less government consumption expenditures and gross investment.
2. The arithmetic average of gross domestic product and of gross domestic income, deflated by the implicit price deflator for GDP.
3. Food excludes personal consumption expenditures for purchased meals and beverages, which are classified in food services.

4. Market-based PCE is a supplemental measure that is based on household expenditures for which there are observable price measures. It excludes most imputed transactions (for example, financial services furnished without payment) and the final consumption expenditures of nonprofit institutions serving households.

Note. Percent changes for real estimates are calculated from corresponding quantity indexes presented in NIPA tables 1.1.3, 1.2.3, 1.4.3, and 1.7.3. Percent changes in price estimates are calculated from corresponding price indexes presented in NIPA tables 1.1.4, 1.6.4, and 2.3.4.
